</div>

<h2>The Stack That Uses Both</h2>
<p>The most common setup among high-performing outbound teams is not a choice between Clay and Apollo — it's using both together:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Apollo</strong> as the data source (search + export leads)</li>
  <li><strong>Clay</strong> as the enrichment layer (waterfall to fill gaps, add intent signals, generate personalization)</li>
  <li><strong>Instantly or Smartlead</strong> for sending</li>
  <li><strong>HubSpot or Salesforce</strong> for CRM sync</li>
</ol>
<p>This stack costs roughly $350–$500/month for a single rep but produces significantly better results than Apollo alone — particularly on reply rates, which typically improve 2–3x when personalization is based on real-time research rather than static data.</p>

